{"_attachments":{},"_id":"use-latest-callback","_rev":"951374-61f28f14575b7399aa0bccd6","author":{"name":"Satyajit Sahoo","email":"satyajit.happy@gmail.com"},"description":"React hook which returns the latest callback without changing the reference","dist-tags":{"latest":"0.3.4"},"license":"MIT","maintainers":[{"name":"satya164","email":"satyajit.happy@gmail.com"}],"name":"use-latest-callback","readme":"# use-latest-callback\n\nReact hook which returns the latest callback without changing the reference.\n\nThis is useful for scenarios such as event listeners where you may not want to resubscribe when the callback changes.\n\n## Installation\n\nOpen a Terminal in the project root and run:\n\n```sh\nnpm install use-latest-callback\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThe `useLatestCallback` hook accepts a function as its argument and returns a function that preserves its reference across renders.\n\n```js\nimport useLatestCallback from 'use-latest-callback';\n\n// ...\n\nfunction MyComponent() {\n  const callback = useLatestCallback((value) => {\n    console.log('Changed', value);\n  });\n\n  React.useEffect(() => {\n    someEvent.addListener(callback);\n\n    return () => someEvent.removeListener(callback);\n  }, [callback]);\n\n  return <>{/* whatever */}</>;\n}\n```\n\nIt's important to note that the callback is not intended to be called during the render phase. Only call the callback in response to an event.\n","time":{"created":"2022-01-27T12:24:52.890Z","modified":"2026-05-13T13:24:33.352Z","0.1.1":"2021-06-14T03:03:19.681Z","0.1.2":"2022-06-02T11:56:27.888Z","0.1.3":"2022-06-02T12:01:21.850Z","0.1.4":"2022-06-02T19:16:28.220Z","0.1.5":"2022-08-24T00:03:15.374Z","0.1.6":"2023-04-14T12:19:00.986Z","0.1.7":"2023-10-19T14:37:53.769Z","0.1.8":"2023-11-09T14:24:28.927Z","0.1.9":"2023-11-09T16:39:56.302Z","0.1.10":"2024-07-07T10:54:18.363Z","0.1.11":"2024-07-07T11:42:21.299Z","0.2.0":"2024-07-10T11:03:33.609Z","0.2.1":"2024-07-10T11:26:32.652Z","0.2.2":"2024-11-14T12:30:16.949Z","0.2.